        Ingredients:
        - "raw": The full original string of the ingredient translated to ${targetLangName} (e.g., "250g of fresh tomatoes").
        - "name": Just the item name in ${targetLangName} (e.g., "Tomatoes").
        - "amount": Just the quantity (e.g., "250").
        - "unit": Just the unit (e.g., "g").
        
        MATCHING:
        I am providing a list of existing ingredients in my database:
        ${ingredientsJson}
        
        If a parsed ingredient matches an existing one, include its "id" in the "existingId" field.
        
        STRICT RULES FOR MATCHING:
        - Only match if it is the EXACT same ingredient.
        - NEVER match different variants (e.g., do NOT match "Onion" with "Spring Onion", or "Butter" with "Peanut Butter").
        - If in doubt, do NOT match; leave "existingId" null.
        - Translations are allowed (e.g., "Zwiebel" (DE) matches "Onion" (EN)), but only if they are the exact same item.
        - Be ultra-conservative. It is better to create a new ingredient than to match an incorrect one.
        
        Categories: Pick from [Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, Snack, Dessert, Healthy, Quick].
        
        NUTRITION (IMPORTANT):
        - Extract calories (kcal), protein (g), carbs (g), and fat (g) per serving.
        - If NOT EXPLICITLY PROVIDED in the text, you MUST ESTIMATE them based on the ingredients and typical portion sizes.
        - If you ESTIMATED them, set "isEstimated" to true. If they were plainly written in the text, set "isEstimated" to false.
        
        DAYS COVERAGE:
        - Estimate how many days this recipe will cover for a household of ${householdSize} people.
        - Assume typical serving sizes.
